name: Zack F
text: The HQ Chapel is a beautiful WWII era building constructed and furnished by German POWs. More importantly it is home to a tightly knit and welcoming church community. It's a great place both to come for a visit or to join as your home church.

name: Glenn Davis
text: Place where you be truly blessed and loving family in the Lord. Come join us and see for yourself you'll be truly blessed and find . What love really is.

name: kathy Jean
text: I was going through a tough time after I lost my love ones. I was going to the library and God touch my heart and mind and said go inside and I will give you peaceful mind. I said Yes Lord ❤️. Now this my happy place I go in clean up the house and leave prayer pamphlets. If you're having a hard time with your kids and kids if you need some one to listen you are welcome to contact me God bless you and your family 🙏💕🙏🏾❤️💕

name: Chanda Mitchell
text: Just a tiny little chapel on the side of the road where you can write your prayer on the paper provided and light a candle if you wish. Kind of neat. I had never seen one before in the United States.
